# Vercel Speed Insights Implementation

## Summary
Successfully implemented Vercel Speed Insights in the React application to enable performance monitoring and real-time web vitals tracking.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Added `@vercel/speed-insights` package (version 1.3.1) to project dependencies
- Updated package.json with the new dependency
- Generated updated package-lock.json with all transitive dependencies

### 2. Component Integration
- Modified `src/App.jsx` to integrate Speed Insights:
  - Added import statement: `import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/react';`
  - Placed `<SpeedInsights />` component at the bottom of the main app container
  - This placement ensures Speed Insights tracks all user interactions throughout the app

## Implementation Details

Following the Vercel Speed Insights documentation for React applications (create-react-app pattern), the SpeedInsights component was added to the main App component. This is a wrapper around the tracking script that provides seamless integration with React.

The component is placed inside the main container div to ensure proper tracking across all routes and user interactions within the application.

